                            <comment id="472259" author="yujian" created="Fri, 19 Sep 2025 20:25:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dongyang&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dongyang&quot;&gt;dongyang&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;br/&gt;
From lustre-initialization-1.autotest.onyx-99vm1.log in &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0575c47a-a460-45a1-9531-0141c04caa22&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0575c47a-a460-45a1-9531-0141c04caa22&lt;/a&gt;, we can see:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;export mgs_HOST=onyx-99vm7
export mds_HOST=onyx-99vm7
export mds1_HOST=onyx-99vm7
export MDSCOUNT=1
export mdsfailover_HOST=onyx-99vm8
export mds1failover_HOST=onyx-99vm8
export MGSNID=onyx-99vm7:onyx-99vm8
export FAILURE_MODE=HARD
export POWER_DOWN=&quot;pm -h powerman --off&quot;
export POWER_UP=&quot;pm -h powerman --on&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;onyx-99vm7 and onyx-99vm8 are MDS failover partner, so both of them were marked as MDS 1.&lt;br/&gt;
The failover test sessions were configured with &quot;FAILURE_MODE=HARD&quot;, which means the test node would be powered off (without unmounting) and failed over to its partner.&lt;br/&gt;
The issue in this ticket is that the previous subtest replay-dual/30 failed over $SINGLEMDS to its partner node, but &lt;tt&gt;at_max_set&lt;/tt&gt; in replay-dual/31 didn&apos;t chose the active node.&lt;br/&gt;
Let me push a patch to resolve it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="471529" author="dongyang" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2025 06:51:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I checked the failed test sessions they are all running failover-part-1,&lt;br/&gt;
and looks like both servers are marked as MDS1, e.g.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/97fa7274-1ba7-4b6e-91da-3975444b33b8&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/97fa7274-1ba7-4b6e-91da-3975444b33b8&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
onyx-99vm7 - MDS 1 (2.15.0.RC2, x86_64)
onyx-99vm8 - MDS 1 (2.15.0.RC2, x86_64)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So when the test scripts trying to set at_max on onyx-99vm7, it failed as console log shows the mds is actually mounted on onyx-99vm8. The test suite log shows the lctl get_param at_max also failed earlier but that didn&apos;t trigger the test case to fail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also checked other succeed replay-dual test_31 sessions, those are showing a different configuration, we have 2 MDS servers but one is designated as MDS 1 and the other as MDS 2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could someone help understand what is failover-part-1 and why it has 2 servers acting as MDS 1?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
